          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "A 220 microgram/cm2 thick 12C target was used which",
                "included a 0.35% impurity of 208Pb."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "TELES",
                "SI",
                "SI"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " A small area delta E - E Si telescope",
                "with thicknesses 5 micrometer and 3 mm respectively,",
                "on one side of the beam centered at 20 degree w.r.t",
                "the beam at a distance of 89.2 mm. The telescope is",
                "used to identify and detect 14C. The energy resolution",
                "of the telescope was 2.4% at 77.8 MeV 12C ions."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "PS"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " On the other side of the beam was a position",
                "sensitive detector (PSD) centered at 20 degree w.r.t",
                "the beam direction at a distance of 101.7 mm. The PSD",
                "was a 300 micro-m single area 8x45 mm2 active region",
                "covering a solid angle of 34.5 mSr at the target",
                "center. The PSD therefore covered an angle of",
                "5.84 - 34.16 degrees. The PSD is used to detect the",
                "alpha particles. The entrance of the PSD was covered",
                "with a 250 micro-m (100 mil) thick Mylar foil to",
                "prevent the entry of heavy ions produced in the",
                "reaction. The energy resolution of the telescope was",
                "50 keV for alpha particles (241Am source) at 5.5 MeV."
              ]
            }
          ],
